IRS990.Desc: AGRICULTURAL ALUMNI SEED IMPROVEMENT ASSOCIATION (AG ALUMNI SEED) HAS WORKED HARD TO GAIN ITS LEADERSHIP POSITION IN THE DEVELOPMENT AND RELEASE OF HIGH PERFORMANCE POPCORN HYBRIDS. WITH THIS POSITION COMES THE RESPONSIBILITY TO PUT ALL OUR AVAILABLE RESOURCES TO WORK IN THE CONTINUATION OF THE WORK THAT'S MADE US WHAT WE ARE TODAY. FROM THE GROUND-BREAKING WORK THAT HAS OCCURRED SINCE 1938, AG ALUMNI SEED HAS ESTABLISHED ITSELF AS THE WORLD'S LEADING SUPPLIER OF HIGH PERFORMING, HIGH QUALITY POPCORN HYBRIDS. IN ADDITION, AG ALUMNI SEED WORKS TO PROMOTE EDUCATION AND RESEARCH ACTIVITIES WITH COOPERATING AGENCIES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Schedule D, Part X, Line 2 FIN 48 (ASC 740) footnote
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Association is exempt from federal and state income taxes under Section 501 (c)(5) of the Internal Revenue Code. Under guidance issued by the FASB with respect to accounting for uncertainty in income taxes as a tax position is recognized as a benefit only if it is "more likely than not" that the tax position would be sustained in a tax examination, with a tax examination being presumed to occur. The amount recognized is the largest amount of tax benefit that is greater than 50% likely of being realized on examination. For tax positions not meeting the "more likely than not" test, no tax benefit is recorded. The Association recognizes interest and penalties related to unrecognized tax benefits in interest expense. The Association has no amounts accrued for interest or penalties as of October 31, 2022 and 2021. The Association is no longer subject to examination by U.S. federal or state taxing authorities for years before 2019. The Association does not expect the total amount of unrecognized tax benefits to significantly change in the next 12 months.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Schedule L, Part IV, Column (d) DESCRIPTION OF TRANSACTION - Lawerence C. Beck
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: LAWRENCE C. BECK IS A DIRECTOR OF AGRICULTURAL ALUMNI SEED IMPROVEMENT ASSOCIATION ("THE ORGANIZATION"); HE IS ALSO THE OWNER OF BECK'S SUPERIOR HYBRIDS AND A TRUSTEE OF BECK'S SUPERIOR HYBRIDS EMPLOYEE PENSION PLAN. DURING THE FISCAL YEAR ENDED OCTOBER 31, 2022, THE ORGANIZATION ENTERED INTO THE FOLLOWING TRANSACTIONS WITH INTERESTED PERSONS: - THE ORGANIZATION MADE LAND RENT FOR FARMLAND AND TOOL SHED PAYMENTS TO BECK'S SUPERIOR HYBRIDS EMPLOYEE PENSION PLAN IN THE AMOUNT OF $107,826. - THE ORGANIZATION PURCHASED SOYBEAN SEEDS FROM BECK'S SUPERIOR HYBRIDS IN THE AMOUNT OF $77,545 ALL TRANSACTIONS ARE MADE PURSUANT TO AN AGREEMENT, ARE ARMS-LENGTH, AND AT FAIR MARKET PRICES. MR. BECK DOES NOT PARTICIPATE IN BOARD DISCUSSION OR APPROVAL OF TRANSACTIONS WITH BECK'S SUPERIOR HYBRIDS OR THE PENSION PLAN. MR. BECK'S POSITION AS A BOARD MEMBER OF THE ORGANIZATION HAS NO EFFECT ON WHETHER THE ORGANIZATION ENTERS INTO TRANSACTIONS WITH OR THE PRICE OF SUCH TRANSACTIONS BETWEEN THE ORGANIZATION AND BECK'S SUPERIOR HYBRIDS OR THE PENSION PLAN.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 6 Classes of members or stockholders
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Members of the board must be duly qualified and acting members of the board of directors of The Purdue Agricultural Alumni Association, Inc. ("PAAA") (a corporation) or duly qualified and acting members of the Seed Improvement Committee of such last named corporation.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 7a Members or stockholders electing members of governing body
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Members elect board of directors at the annual meeting.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 8b Documentation of meetings held by committees of governing body
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The organization does not have any committees with the authority to act on behalf of the governing body.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 11b Review of form 990 by governing body
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A final draft of the full Form 990, including all applicable schedules, is provided to each member of the organization's governing body prior to its filing with the IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 12c Conflict of interest policy
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Annual conflict of interest statements are signed by all board members and officers to disclose any potential conflicts anyone may have. The statements are reviewed by the Board, and anyone with a conflict of interest is required to remove her(him)self from the discussion and voting process related to the conflicting issue.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 15a Process to establish compensation of top management official
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Organization's compensation committee reviews and approves the President's compensation annually each November; at this time, the compensation committee also reviews and approves any raises and bonuses awarded. The compensation committee's deliberation and decision is documented in the meeting minutes. The Compensation committee had an independent compensation study performed in 2022; this data was utilized during November 2022 when the compensation committee reviewed and authorized the salary and bonus information for the president.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 15b Process to establish compensation of other employees
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Annually, the organization's President provides the Compensation Committee a recommendation for compensation adjustments for other officers and key employees. The Compensation Committee reviews and either approves or disapproves the President's recommendation for compensation adjustments. The Compensation Committee's deliberation and decision is documented in the meeting minutes. In November of 2022, the Board was given 2022 survey data for officers and key employees for comparative purposes.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 19 Required documents available to the public
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Governing documents, financial statements, and conflict of interest policies are not required disclosures pursuant to Internal Revenue Code Section 6104; these documents are not available to the public at this time.
